The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Six coastal police stations will be set up to strengthen maritime vigil around the city, the police top brass and home secretary Asok Mohan Chakrabarti decided in a meeting at Writers Buildings on Friday. Three of the police stations will come in South 24-Parganas and one in North 24-Parganas. It was also decided that the security ring will be tightened around railway stations, shopping malls and vital installations.     Actress Swastika Mukherjee, her father Santu Mukherjee and mother Gopa were granted bail by the ninth additional chief judicial magistrates court in Alipore on Friday in a cheating case. The complainant, Ashok Maity, alleged that Swastika and her parents had not repaid a loan of Rs 5 lakh.    Ten workers were injured when a mould exploded in a foundry near Pailan in Bishnupur on Friday morning. Five tenders brought the fire under control in two hours. Seven workers were admitted to a private hospital on EM Bypass. The other three were discharged after first-aid.     The 19th Sonarpur Book Fair was inaugurated on Friday by economist Amiya Bagchi. Bankura district is the theme of the fair, for which 80 stalls have been put up.    Constable Kalipada Dey, 27, was arrested in Behala on Friday for allegedly murdering his wife Tumpa, 25, on Thursday night. Her body was found at their Bangasree Colony residence. Kalipada was arrested after Tumpas parents lodged a complaint alleging that he forced her to take poison.    Jarina Begum, a 35-year-old Garden Reach resident, was admitted to SSKM Hospital with severe burns on Friday afternoon. She told police that her husband Akhtar Ali Khan had tried to set her on fire after a quarrel between the two. Akhtar, a driver for Calcutta Port Trust, is absconding.     South Eastern Railways will run five pairs of superfast winter special trains between Howrah and Puri between December 2 and December 31. The special trains will leave Howrah every Wednesday at 8.55pm and reach Puri at 5.50am the next day.     The Airports Authority of India made a presentation on Calcutta airports modernisation project before members of the Bharat Chamber of Commerce and Industries and the Bengal National Chamber of Commerce and Industries on Friday.                                                                                                                                                                  
